---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Enterprise Services — Starling AIX" description="Starling builds organizational intelligence systems — then makes sure someone in your organization can run them. Every engagement ends with a person, not a report.">

<!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;padding:7rem 0 6rem;" class="grid-bg">
  <div class="hero-glow"></div>
  <span class="corner-mark cm-tl">+</span>
  <span class="corner-mark cm-tr">+</span>
  <div class="container" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">

    <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">Starling AIX · Enterprise Services</p>

    <h1 class="heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.08"
        style="font-size:clamp(3rem,8vw,5.5rem);margin:0 0 1.5rem;max-width:820px;letter-spacing:-0.04em;">
      We build it. We teach it. We <em>staff</em> it.
    </h1>

    <p class="fade-up" data-delay="0.15"
       style="font-size:1.05rem;color:#71717a;line-height:1.75;max-width:540px;margin:0 0 2.5rem;">
      Starling builds organisational intelligence systems — then makes sure someone in your organisation can run them. Every engagement ends with a person, not a report.
    </p>

    <div class="fade-up" data-delay="0.2" style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="https://calendly.com/starlingaix" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Discovery Call →</a>
      <a href="#how-we-work" class="btn btn-ghost">See How We Work</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── The Mach 1 Problem ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">1.0 · The Mach 1 Problem</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Your AI works. Your org can't absorb what it produces.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Decisions accelerate past governance. Knowledge fragments across tools. Context evaporates between sessions. The technology succeeds and the organisation breaks.
        </p>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.13" style="margin-bottom:0;">
          AI memory systems extract patterns from your conversations and harden them over time. The Org Brain is persistent by design. The difference is whether you govern the system — or the system governs you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Wide diagnostic mockup -->
    <div class="wide-mock fade-up" data-delay="0.18">
      <div class="mock-bar">
        <span class="mock-dot r"></span><span class="mock-dot y"></span><span class="mock-dot g"></span>
        <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.7rem;color:#3f3f46;margin-left:0.75rem;">Org Brain Diagnostic — Governance Readiness</span>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:2rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:0.75rem;" class="diag-grid">
        {[
          { label: 'Knowledge Fragmentation', score: 72, status: 'Critical', color: '#ef4444' },
          { label: 'Decision Velocity', score: 48, status: 'At Risk', color: '#f97316' },
          { label: 'Context Persistence', score: 21, status: 'Failing', color: '#ef4444' },
          { label: 'Memory Governance', score: 0, status: 'Not Configured', color: '#3f3f46' },
          { label: 'Org Brain Coverage', score: 0, status: 'Not Started', color: '#3f3f46' },
        ].map(({ label, score, status, color }) => (
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.25rem;padding:0.75rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);">
            <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.72rem;color:#52525b;min-width:200px;">{label}</span>
            <div style="flex:1;height:4px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);border-radius:2px;overflow:hidden;">
              <div style={`height:100%;width:${score}%;background:${color};border-radius:2px;`}></div>
            </div>
            <span style={`font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:${color};min-width:100px;text-align:right;`}>{status}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem 2rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;">
        <span style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#71717a;">Overall readiness score:</span>
        <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.875rem;color:#ef4444;font-weight:600;">28 / 100</span>
        <span class="badge badge-neutral" style="margin-left:auto;">Run diagnostic in session 1</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── How We Work ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="how-we-work" class="feat-section" style="background:#030303;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">2.0 · How We Work</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Three ways to build organisational intelligence.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Every engagement produces a working system and a certified person to run it. Pick your entry point. Every path leads to the same destination: a Domain Language Model your organisation owns.
        </p>
        <div class="feat-ctas fade-up" data-delay="0.14">
          <a href="https://calendly.com/starlingaix" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Call →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="services-grid">

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2.5rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          <span class="badge">01</span>
          <span style="color:#3f3f46;font-size:0.8rem;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">Done For You</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="heading-upright" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin:0 0 1rem;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Build Your Org Brain</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
          Starling builds your organisational intelligence system directly. C-suite immersion. Guided extraction. Your values, positioning, processes, and culture codified into persistent memory.
        </p>
        <div style="padding:1rem 1.25rem;background:rgba(249,115,22,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.15);border-radius:8px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#f97316;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin:0 0 0.3rem;text-transform:uppercase;">Deliverable</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#a1a1aa;margin:0;">Working Org Brain + certified System Librarian (internal or placed)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="padding:2.5rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          <span class="badge">02</span>
          <span style="color:#3f3f46;font-size:0.8rem;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">License</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="heading-upright" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin:0 0 1rem;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Cognitive Design Program</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
          License the methodology to run at scale inside your organisation, accelerator, or consulting practice. We train your trainers. You certify your people. The curriculum is yours to deploy.
        </p>
        <div style="padding:1rem 1.25rem;background:rgba(249,115,22,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.15);border-radius:8px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#f97316;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin:0 0 0.3rem;text-transform:uppercase;">Deliverable</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#a1a1aa;margin:0;">Per-cohort license + certified facilitators who deliver the program internally</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.12" style="padding:2.5rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          <span class="badge">03</span>
          <span style="color:#3f3f46;font-size:0.8rem;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">Every Gate</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="heading-upright" style="font-size:1.3rem;margin:0 0 1rem;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Certify or Place</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.8;margin:0 0 1.5rem;">
          At the end of every engagement, your organisation gets a person — either trained from within or placed from the Starling network. You don't just get a methodology. You get the human who runs it.
        </p>
        <div style="padding:1rem 1.25rem;background:rgba(249,115,22,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.15);border-radius:8px;">
          <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#f97316;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin:0 0 0.3rem;text-transform:uppercase;">Deliverable</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#a1a1aa;margin:0;">System Librarian, Cognitive Designer, or Chief Intelligence Officer — yours to keep</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── The Curriculum ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="position:relative;" class="grid-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">3.0 · The Curriculum</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Eight sprints. Three certifications.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          The Cognitive Design Accelerator takes an organisation from zero to full organisational intelligence — codified, connected, and governed. Each certification gate is a natural stopping point with a complete deliverable.
        </p>
        <div class="feat-ctas fade-up" data-delay="0.14">
          <a href="/cognitive-design" class="btn btn-ghost">Explore Full Curriculum →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.5rem;">

      {[
        {
          badge: 'System Librarian',
          meta: 'Sprints 1–2 · 9 weeks',
          gate: 'Build and govern an Org Brain. For most startups and mid-market companies, this is the complete package.',
          sprints: [
            ['Sprint 1', 'Innovation System', 'Identity, Market, Innovation, Brand — the First Fifteen Constitutional Memories.'],
            ['Sprint 2', 'Applied Intelligence', 'Deep strategy, active project architecture, organisational learning.'],
          ],
        },
        {
          badge: 'Cognitive Designer',
          meta: 'Sprints 3–5 · 12 weeks',
          gate: 'Design how an organisation thinks. Build systems that compound. Connect knowledge to enterprise infrastructure.',
          sprints: [
            ['Sprint 3', 'Optimisation System', 'Productivity, Workflow, Process, Culture — how decisions get made.'],
            ['Sprint 4', 'Cognitive System', 'System configuration, dual metrics, all 28 Constitutional Memories complete.'],
            ['Sprint 5', 'Translation System', 'Connect your Org Brain to SAP, Salesforce, Workday, and 250+ integrations.'],
          ],
        },
        {
          badge: 'Chief Intelligence Officer',
          meta: 'Sprints 6–8 · 8 weeks',
          gate: 'Architect, deploy, and govern enterprise-wide organisational intelligence responsibly.',
          sprints: [
            ['Sprint 6', 'Starling OS', 'Operating prompt design, architecture, constitutional memory, governance.'],
            ['Sprint 7', 'Org Strategy', 'Buy-in, deployment, executive communication — the C-suite function.'],
            ['Sprint 8', 'Governance & Impact', 'AI governance, social impact, the responsibility framework.'],
          ],
        },
      ].map(({ badge, meta, gate, sprints }, idx) => (
        <div class="card fade-up" data-delay={`${idx * 0.08}`} style="padding:0;overflow:hidden;">
          <div style="padding:1.5rem 2rem;background:rgba(249,115,22,0.04);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.12);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <span class="badge">{badge}</span>
            <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#52525b;">{meta}</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:0;" class="sprint-grid">
            {sprints.map(([label, title, body], i) => (
              <div style={`padding:1.5rem 2rem;${i < sprints.length - 1 ? 'border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);' : ''}`}>
                <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#3f3f46;margin:0 0 0.4rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;">{label}</p>
                <h4 style="font-size:0.95rem;color:#e4e4e7;margin:0 0 0.3rem;font-weight:600;">{title}</h4>
                <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#71717a;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">{body}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div style="padding:1.25rem 2rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);background:rgba(249,115,22,0.02);">
            <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#a1a1aa;margin:0;"><span style="color:#f97316;">☆ Gate: </span>{gate}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Corporate Licensing ────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">4.0 · Corporate Licensing</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          License the methodology. Scale without us.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Per-cohort licensing for organisations that need Cognitive Design at workforce scale. We deliver the first cohort directly. Your certified facilitators deliver every cohort after.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="overflow-x:auto;" class="fade-up" data-delay="0.14">
      <table class="ptable" style="min-width:680px;">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th></th>
            <th>Sprint License</th>
            <th>Program License</th>
            <th>Enterprise License</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {[
            ['Curriculum', 'Sprints 1–2', 'Sprints 3–5', 'Sprints 6–8'],
            ['Certification', 'System Librarian', 'Cognitive Designer', 'Chief Intelligence Officer'],
            ['Cohort Size', '15–25 participants', '8–15 participants', '3–8 participants'],
            ['Duration', '9 weeks', '12 weeks', '8 weeks'],
            ['Cohort License', '$25,000', '$50,000', '$75,000'],
            ['Per-Seat Certification', '$500', '$1,500', '$5,000'],
          ].map(([feat, a, b, c]) => (
            <tr>
              <td>{feat}</td>
              <td>{a}</td>
              <td>{b}</td>
              <td>{c}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Who This Is For ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="background:#030303;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">5.0 · Who This Is For</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Three markets. One methodology.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Cognitive Design is a licensing model, not a SaaS subscription. Organisations, accelerators, and consulting firms all deploy the same curriculum — at different scales, with different entry points.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="markets-grid">

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2rem;">
        <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;display:inline-flex;">Enterprise</span>
        <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;color:#3f3f46;margin:0 0 1rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;">CHRO · CIO · VP AI Strategy</p>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem;">
          Organisations deploying AI at scale who need structured knowledge architecture, not just more tools. Train 20 or 2,000.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#52525b;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">
          <strong style="color:#a1a1aa;">Model:</strong> Sprint License pilot → Program License for facilitator corps → Enterprise License for leadership.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="padding:2rem;">
        <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;display:inline-flex;">Accelerators</span>
        <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;color:#3f3f46;margin:0 0 1rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;">Program Director · Managing Partner</p>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem;">
          Give every startup in your batch a working Org Brain by demo day. Their AI produces strategically coherent output — not generic decks.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#52525b;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">
          <strong style="color:#a1a1aa;">Model:</strong> Sprint License per batch. Each startup leaves with a working DLM and a certified System Librarian.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.12" style="padding:2rem;">
        <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;display:inline-flex;">Consulting Firms</span>
        <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;color:#3f3f46;margin:0 0 1rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;">Practice Lead · MD of AI/Digital</p>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1rem;">
          Add organisational intelligence to your AI transformation practice. Certify your consultants. Deliver Org Brain builds to clients under your brand.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#52525b;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">
          <strong style="color:#a1a1aa;">Model:</strong> Program License to certify consultants → consultants deliver Sprint License engagements. 3–6× markup.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Exit Guarantee ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">6.0 · The Exit Guarantee</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Every engagement ends with a person.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          At every certification gate, you have two options. Either way, your organisation gets the human capability to sustain what was built. No report. No slide deck. A person who runs the system.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="guarantee-grid">

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2rem;">
        <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;display:inline-flex;">Option A</span>
        <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;color:#fff;margin:0 0 0.75rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">Certify someone inside your org.</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1.25rem;">
          An internal employee earns the credential through demonstrated mastery — not attendance. They own the knowledge, the tools, and the ongoing governance.
        </p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;">
          {[
            ['System Librarian', '$65–$85K'],
            ['Cognitive Designer', '$95–$120K'],
            ['Chief Intelligence Officer', '$150–$200K+'],
          ].map(([role, comp]) => (
            <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:0.6rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
              <span style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#a1a1aa;">{role}</span>
              <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.78rem;color:#f97316;">{comp}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.08" style="padding:2rem;">
        <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;display:inline-flex;">Option B</span>
        <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;color:#fff;margin:0 0 0.75rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">We place someone from our network.</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 1.25rem;">
          Starling places a pre-certified professional from the broader talent network. Same credentials, same capability — ready to operate from day one.
        </p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;">
          {[
            ['System Librarian', '$65–$85K'],
            ['Cognitive Designer', '$95–$120K'],
            ['Chief Intelligence Officer', '$150–$200K+'],
          ].map(([role, comp]) => (
            <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:0.6rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
              <span style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#a1a1aa;">{role}</span>
              <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.78rem;color:#f97316;">{comp}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── DLM Value Prop ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="background:#030303;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">7.0 · What You Get</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Every engagement produces a Domain Language Model.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          A DLM is what happens when a large language model meets your Org Brain. It doesn't know "business." It knows <em>your</em> business. Four multiplicative factors — remove any one and the product is zero.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="dlm-factors">
      {[
        ['LLM', 'Raw Intelligence', 'Claude, GPT, Gemini — powerful but generic. They know everything about the world and nothing about your business.'],
        ['MCP', 'The Connection', 'Anthropic\'s open protocol. Free for everyone. Makes the LLM replaceable and your intelligence the asset.'],
        ['UCA', 'The Architecture', 'Universal Cognitive Architecture — 11 cognates, 4 memory tiers, semantic addressing. The free, open standard.'],
        ['ORG BRAIN', 'Your Knowledge', 'Your sovereign repository — Persistent Memories, Active Work, Extracted Wisdom — governed by Starling OS.'],
      ].map(([label, title, body], i) => (
        <div class="card fade-up" data-delay={`${i * 0.05}`} style="padding:1.75rem;display:flex;gap:1.25rem;align-items:flex-start;">
          <span class="badge" style="flex-shrink:0;">{label}</span>
          <div>
